Here’s a TekAutomate Steps UI flow to configure CAN FD on a Tektronix MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope, using B1 as the CAN FD source, CH2 as the input, 500 kbps bitrate, and ISO standard. This uses only real TekAutomate step types and verified SCPI commands.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "id": "connect_scope",
      "title": "Connect to Oscilloscope"
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_canfd_bus",
      "title": "Set Bus Type to CAN FD on B1",
      "params": {
        "command": "BUS:TYPE B1,CANFD"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_canfd_source",
      "title": "Set CAN FD Source to CH2",
      "params": {
        "command": "BUS:B1:SOURCE CH2"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_canfd_bitrate",
      "title": "Set CAN FD Bitrate to 500 kbps",
      "params": {
        "command": "BUS:B1:CANFD:BITRate 500000"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_canfd_standard",
      "title": "Set CAN FD Standard to ISO",
      "params": {
        "command": "BUS:B1:CANFD:STANDARD ISO"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "id": "disconnect_scope",
      "title": "Disconnect from Oscilloscope"
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow will:
1. Connect to the oscilloscope.
2. Set Bus B1 to CAN FD.
3. Set the CAN FD source to CH2.
4. Set the bitrate to 500 kbps.
5. Set the CAN FD standard to ISO.
6. Disconnect from the oscilloscope.

If you need to save a screenshot or waveform after setup, let me know!

